## File 4 — `.github/workflows/nrt.yml`

```yaml
name: NRT - Non Regression Tests

# workflow_dispatch means you trigger it MANUALLY from GitHub UI
# and you can pass inputs (like the token) at trigger time
on:
  workflow_dispatch:
    inputs:
      auth_token:
        description: 'Paste Bearer token from Swagger here'
        required: true
        type: string
      base_url:
        description: 'Target environment URL'
        required: true
        default: 'https://your-uat-server.com'
        type: string

jobs:
  nrt:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest

    steps:
      - name: Checkout code
        uses: actions/checkout@v3

      - name: Set up JDK 17
        uses: actions/setup-java@v3
        with:
          java-version: '17'
          distribution: 'temurin'

      - name: Run NRT Engine
        # Pass the inputs as environment variables
        # The test reads them via System.getenv()
        env:
          AUTH_TOKEN: ${{ inputs.auth_token }}
          BASE_URL: ${{ inputs.base_url }}
        run: ./mvnw test -Dtest=NrtEngine

      - name: Publish Test Report
        # Always run this step even if tests fail
        # So you always see the report
        if: always()
        uses: dorny/test-reporter@v1
        with:
          name: NRT Results
          path: target/surefire-reports/*.xml
          reporter: java-junit
```

