## Question 1 — Scaling to All APIs

Right now the engine has this hardcoded:
```java
String flowPath = NRT_BASE + "currencyApi/";
```

When we scale, we change it to **auto-discover all folders:**

```
nrt/
  currencyApi/        ← picks this up automatically
  createUser/         ← picks this up automatically
  getAccounts/        ← picks this up automatically
  deleteTransaction/  ← picks this up automatically
```

The engine loops through every folder, finds `request.json` and `expected-response.json`, and runs a test for each one. **You never touch the Java file again.** You only add new folders.

We'll do this in iteration 2. Not now.

---

## Question 2 — UAT vs DEV separately

You're exactly right. The URL is the only thing that changes between environments. Everything else — the request, the expected response, the validation mode — stays the same.

This is handled by just passing a different `BASE_URL` when you trigger the workflow:

```
DEV run:
  BASE_URL = https://dev.your-server.com
  AUTH_TOKEN = dev token from Swagger

UAT run:
  BASE_URL = https://uat.your-server.com
  AUTH_TOKEN = uat token from Swagger
```

The workflow already handles this because `BASE_URL` is an input parameter you fill in manually when triggering. So same code, same JSON files, different environment = different run.

---

## Summary

```
Scale to all APIs  → auto folder discovery, iteration 2
Multi environment  → already handled, just change BASE_URL input
JSON files         → never change regardless of environment
Java engine        → never changes after iteration 2
```

